  "prompt": "If I delete someone on Snapchat that I have a streak with, and my account is available for everyone to snap/chat me, will that erase the streak?",
  "response": "If you delete someone on Snapchat with whom you have an ongoing streak, the streak will be lost. Streaks are maintained by continuous daily interactions between both parties. When you delete someone, it breaks the connection required to sustain the streak. Even if your account is set to public, the specific interaction with that individual is what counts for maintaining the streak, and deleting them disrupts this interaction.",
